nl_questions: Which clubs have more seasons in the top division and at least one top division title, excluding those without titles?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Club`, `Position in 2012â€“13`, `Number of seasons in top division`, `Number of seasons in the Premier League`, `Top division titles`
FROM `table_1_11250_4`

AND `Top division titles` > 0
ORDER BY `Number of seasons in top division` DESC, `Top division titles` DESC;

nl_questions: What is the total number of appearances for each player whose career includes the years 1980s or 1990s?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Player`, COUNT(`Player`) as `Number of Appearances`
FROM (
    SELECT `Player`
    FROM `table_1_11545282_4`
    WHERE `Years for Jazz` LIKE '%198%'
    UNION
    SELECT `Player`
    FROM `table_1_11545282_4`
    WHERE `Years for Jazz` LIKE '%199%'
) AS `Appearances`
GROUP BY `Player`
ORDER BY `Number of Appearances` DESC;

    `Case/Suffix`,
    `we two` AS `WeTwo`,

nl_questions: What are the years, tournaments played, cuts made, wins, seconds, top tens, best finishes, earnings, money list ranks, scoring averages, and scoring ranks for which the earnings exceed $100,000, have at least one win, and have played more than ten tournaments, ordered by cumulative earnings per tournament in descending order?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Year`, `Tournaments played`, `Cuts made*`, `Wins`, `2nd`, `Top 10s`, `Best finish`, `Earnings ($)`, `Money list rank`, `Scoring average`, `Scoring rank`
FROM (
    SELECT `Year`, `Tournaments played`, `Cuts made*`, `Wins`, `2nd`, `Top 10s`, `Best finish`, `Earnings ($)`, `Money list rank`, `Scoring average`, `Scoring rank`,
           SUM(`Earnings ($)` * (`Wins` + `2nd` + `Top 10s`) / `Tournaments played`) OVER (ORDER BY `Year`) AS `Cumulative earnings per tournament`
    FROM `table_1_10021158_3`
) AS `subquery`
WHERE `Earnings ($)` > 100000 AND `Wins` > 0 AND `Tournaments played` > 10
ORDER BY `Cumulative earnings per tournament` DESC;

nl_questions: What is the average population of counties where there are more than one habitually Irish-speaking population?

SELECT `County`, COUNT(`Irish speakers`) AS `Number_of_Irish_speakers`, AVG(`Population`) AS `Average_Population`

nl_questions: In descending order of power, which Volvo V70 engines have more power than the average power of all engines?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Model name`, `Power (ps)` as Power, `Torque (Nm@rpm)` as Torque, `Displacement (cmÂ³)` as Displacement, `Engine code`, `Comment`
FROM `Volvo V70`
WHERE `Power (ps)` > (SELECT AVG(`Power (ps)`) FROM `Volvo V70`)
ORDER BY `Power (ps)` DESC;

nl_questions: What is the total average production per commodity, found by adding the annual averages from 2001-02 to 2006-07, with the results ordered from the highest total to the lowest?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Commodity`, AVG(`2001-02`) + AVG(`2002-03`) + AVG(`2003-04`) + AVG(`2004-05`) + AVG(`2005-06`) + AVG(`2006-07`) AS `Average Production`
FROM `table_1_1057262_1`
GROUP BY `Commodity`
ORDER BY `Average Production` DESC;

nl_questions: What is the average, maximum, minimum number of viewers per season, along with the count and total number of episodes for each season?

SELECT 
    `Season`, 
    AVG(`Viewers (in millions)`) AS `Average Viewers`, 
    MAX(`Viewers (in millions)`) AS `Max Viewers`, 
    MIN(`Viewers (in millions)`) AS `Min Viewers`, 
    COUNT(*) AS `Number of Seasons`, 
    SUM(`Episodes`) AS `Total Episodes`
FROM 
    `table_1_10819266_8`
GROUP BY 
    `Season`;

nl_questions: What is the cumulative total of episodes for each character, encompassing their entire run on the series?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Character`, COUNT(`Episode`) as `Total_Episodes`
FROM (
    SELECT `Character`, SUBSTR(`First Episode`, 4) as `Episode`
    FROM `table_1_11210576_3`
    UNION ALL
    SELECT `Character`, SUBSTR(`Final Episode`, 4) as `Episode`
    FROM `table_1_11210576_3`
) AS `Episodes`
GROUP BY `Character`
ORDER BY `Total_Episodes` DESC;

nl_questions: How many times does each dance/song appear, and what is the average score for each dance/song, arranged by the frequency of appearance and average score in descending order?
sql_queries:
SELECT 
    `Dance/song`, 
    COUNT(`Dance/song`) AS `Number of dances per song`, 
    AVG(`Total`) AS `Average total score`, 
    MAX(`Total`) AS `Highest total score`, 
    MIN(`Total`) AS `Lowest total score`
FROM 
    `table_1_1014319_1`
GROUP BY 
    `Dance/song`
ORDER BY 
    `Number of dances per song` DESC,
    `Average total score` DESC;

nl_questions: For each winning team from 2000 to 2010, what were their total wins and the average crowd size at their games?
sql_queries:
SELECT `WinningTeam`, COUNT(*) as `TotalWins`, AVG(`GF Attendance`) as `AverageAttendance`
FROM (
    SELECT `WinningTeam`, `GF Attendance`
    FROM `table_1_11236195_5`
    WHERE `Season` >= 2000 AND `Season` <= 2010
)
GROUP BY `WinningTeam`
ORDER BY `TotalWins` DESC, `AverageAttendance` DESC;

nl_questions: What are the names of the top performers based on their batting averages, and how many players fall into this category?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Player`, `Average`, COUNT(`Player`) as `Number of Players`
FROM (
    SELECT `Player`, `Average`
    FROM `table_1_10621256_1`
    WHERE `Average` > (
        SELECT AVG(`Average`)
        FROM `table_1_10621256_1`
    )
) AS `Subquery`
GROUP BY `Player`
ORDER BY `Number of Players` DESC;
comments: group by players will make it always return 1 for all rather than the actual count

nl_questions: What is the average number of seats won per election, the range of seats won across all elections, the total number of elections, and how many times PQ and Liberal majorities occurred?
sql_queries:
SELECT 
    `# of candidates`, 
    AVG(`# of seats won`) AS `Average Seats Won`, 
    MAX(`# of seats won`) - MIN(`# of seats won`) AS `Seat Range`, 
    COUNT(*) AS `Number of Elections`, 
    SUM(CASE WHEN `Result` = 'PQ majority' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `PQ Majority Elections`, 
    SUM(CASE WHEN `Result` = 'Liberal majority' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Liberal Majority Elections`, 
    SUM(CASE WHEN `Result` = 'Liberal minority' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Liberal Minority Elections`
FROM 
    `table_1_106367_2`;

nl_questions: What is the combined count of all diseases for each year?
sql_queries:
SELECT 
    `Year`, 
    SUM(`Typhus`) + SUM(`Typhoid fever`) + SUM(`Relapsing fever`) + SUM(`Smallpox`) + SUM(`Malaria`) AS `Total Disease Incidence`
FROM 
    `table_1_1007688_1`
GROUP BY 
    `Year`
ORDER BY 
    `Year` ASC;

SELECT COUNT(*) as `Number of Celebrities`, AVG(`Viewers`) as `Average Viewers`, `Director` as `Most Frequent Director`
FROM (
    SELECT `Celebrity`, `Director`, `Viewers`
    FROM `table_1_11642945_1`
    WHERE `Viewers`!= 'N/A'
) AS `Filtered Data`
GROUP BY `Director`
ORDER BY `Average Viewers` DESC
LIMIT 1;
comments: the group by director is wrong here because it is asking for the most overall, so returning per director is misleading

nl_questions: For each finishing position, what is the sum of Points awarded (Platinum), Points awarded (Gold), Points awarded (Silver), and Points awarded (Satellite)?

FROM `table_1_11254821_2`
GROUP BY `Finishing position`
ORDER BY Total_Points DESC;

nl_questions: For each season, how many episodes were there, what was the average U.S. viewership, the minimum, and the maximum?
sql_queries:
SELECT 
    `Season #`, 
    COUNT(`Series #`) AS `Number of Episodes`, 
    AVG(`U.S. viewers (millions)`) AS `Average Viewers`, 
    MIN(`U.S. viewers (millions)`) AS `Minimum Viewers`, 
    MAX(`U.S. viewers (millions)`) AS `Maximum Viewers`
FROM 
    `table_1_10749143_2`
GROUP BY 
    `Season #`
ORDER BY 
    `Season #`;

nl_questions: Which venues had a total greater than the average total, along with their average, highest, lowest, total, last year's total, and whether their total increased ('+') or decreased ('-') compared to the previous year?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Venue`, `Average`, `Highest`, `Lowest`, `Total`, `Last Year`, `Up/Down`
FROM (
    SELECT `Venue`, AVG(`Average`) AS `Average`, MAX(`Highest`) AS `Highest`, MIN(`Lowest`) AS `Lowest`, SUM(`Total`) AS `Total`, 
           LAG(`Last Year`) OVER (ORDER BY `Total` DESC) AS `Last Year`, 
           CASE WHEN LAG(`Last Year`) OVER (ORDER BY `Total` DESC) > `Last Year` THEN '+'|| (LAG(`Last Year`) OVER (ORDER BY `Total` DESC) - `Last Year`)
                WHEN LAG(`Last Year`) OVER (ORDER BY `Total` DESC) < `Last Year` THEN '-'|| (`Last Year` - LAG(`Last Year`) OVER (ORDER BY `Total` DESC))
                ELSE 'N/A'
           END AS `Up/Down`
    FROM `table_1_1161065_28`
)
WHERE `Total` > (SELECT AVG(`Total`) FROM `table_1_1161065_28`);

nl_questions: Which year had the championship with the highest winning score and what was the margin of victory and the names of the runner-up(s), if any?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Year`, `Championship`, `54 holes`, `Winning score`, `Margin of victory`, `Runner(s)-up`
FROM (
    SELECT `Year`, `Championship`, `54 holes`, `Winning score`, `Margin of victory`, `Runner(s)-up`,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY `Year` ORDER BY `Winning score` DESC) as rn
    FROM `table_1_11570261_2`
) subquery
WHERE rn = 1;

SELECT 
    `Capita`, 
    AVG(`Prim. energy`) AS `Average Primary Energy`,
    SUM(`Production`) AS `Total Production`,
    MAX(`Export`) AS `Max Export`,
    MIN(`Electricity`) AS `Min Electricity`
FROM 
    `table_1_10580575_1`
GROUP BY 
    `Capita`
ORDER BY 
    `Average Primary Energy` DESC;

nl_questions: How many games did each team play, what was their average score per game, and how many wins did they have, sorted by the number of wins in descending order and then by the average score in descending order?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Team`, COUNT(`Score`) as `Total Games`, AVG(CAST(REPLACE(SUBSTR(`Score`, 4), ',', '') AS REAL)) as `Average Score`, SUM(CASE WHEN `Score` LIKE '%W%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as `Wins`
FROM `table_1_10812293_4`
GROUP BY `Team`

nl_questions: What is the top constructor based on the number of races they won between March 21 and August 22?
sql_queries:

FROM (
    SELECT `Constructor`, COUNT(*) as `Wins`

    )

)
ORDER BY `Wins` DESC
LIMIT 1;

    `Conference`, 
    SUM(`# of Bids`) as `Total Bids`, 
    AVG(`Win %`) as `Average Win Percentage`,
    COUNT(*) as `Number of Conferences`
FROM 
    `table_1_10722506_6`
GROUP BY 
    `Conference`
ORDER BY 
    `Total Bids` DESC, 
    `Average Win Percentage` DESC;

    `table_1_103084_4`

nl_questions: What are the tournaments along with their total purses and the sum of first prizes, grouped by tournament and ordered by the total first prize in descending order?

nl_questions: For each champion listed in the table, how many times they have been the winner, what is the average score of their games, what was the lowest score they achieved, and what was the highest score they achieved, sorted by the number of wins in descending order?
sql_queries:
SELECT 
    `Champion`, 
    COUNT(*) as `Number of Wins`, 
    AVG(`Score`) as `Average Score`, 
    MIN(`Score`) as `Lowest Score`, 
    MAX(`Score`) as `Highest Score`
FROM 
    `table_1_11214772_1`
GROUP BY 
    `Champion`
ORDER BY 
    `Number of Wins` DESC;

nl_questions: What locations have a total open hours greater than the average total open hours?
sql_queries:
SELECT `Location`, `Monday`, `Tuesday`, `Wednesday`, `Thursday`, `Friday`, `Saturday`, `Sunday`
FROM (
    SELECT `Location`, `Monday`, `Tuesday`, `Wednesday`, `Thursday`, `Friday`, `Saturday`, `Sunday`,
           `Monday` + `Tuesday` + `Wednesday` + `Thursday` + `Friday` + `Saturday` + `Sunday` AS `Total Hours`
    FROM `table_1_11019212_1`
) AS `Subquery`
WHERE `Total Hours` > (
    SELECT AVG(`Total Hours`)
    FROM (
        SELECT `Location`, `Monday`, `Tuesday`, `Wednesday`, `Thursday`, `Friday`, `Saturday`, `Sunday`,
               `Monday` + `Tuesday` + `Wednesday` + `Thursday` + `Friday` + `Saturday` + `Sunday` AS `Total Hours`
        FROM `table_1_11019212_1`
    ) AS `AverageHours`
);

nl_questions: What is the total number of railbuses built, their average number built per entry, the total number built in Scotland, and the latest withdrawal date?

FROM `BR Railbuses`;
